Your `ErrorController` is fine. The reason you see the XML error page is that an exception happens inside `/auth/callback` **before** your code redirects to `/error/technical`. The platform `PfExceptionHandler` catches it first and returns its own XML response.

Handle callback errors inside `AuthController` and redirect explicitly to your UI error page.

```java
@GetMapping("/callback")
public void callback(
        @RequestParam String code,
        @RequestParam String state,
        HttpServletResponse response) throws IOException {

    try {
        AuthResult authResult = authService.handleCallback(code, state);

        Cookie cookie = new Cookie(
                "ARTHUR_SESSION",
                authResult.getSessionId());

        cookie.setHttpOnly(true);
        cookie.setSecure(true);
        cookie.setPath("/");
        cookie.setDomain("kubernetes.localhost");
        cookie.setMaxAge(3600);

        response.addCookie(cookie);

        String redirectUrl = "/arthur-core/sales-points?appId="
                + URLEncoder.encode(
                        authResult.getAppId(),
                        StandardCharsets.UTF_8);

        response.sendRedirect(redirectUrl);

    } catch (Exception exception) {
        log.error("Authentication callback failed", exception);
        response.sendRedirect("/arthur-core/error/technical");
    }
}
```

Use your actual context path consistently. Your screenshots show the app is under:

```text
/arthur-core
```

So this is important:

```java
response.sendRedirect("/arthur-core/error/technical");
```

not just:

```java
response.sendRedirect("/error/technical");
```

That lets the browser reach:

```text
https://arthur-core.kubernetes.localhost/arthur-core/error/technical
```

and render `views/ui-error`.

## `ErrorController` coverage

A direct unit test is enough. No need for MockMvc.

```java
@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)
class ErrorControllerTest {

    private final ErrorController errorController =
            new ErrorController();

    @Test
    void technicalError_shouldReturnTechnicalErrorPage() {
        ModelAndView result = errorController.technicalError();

        assertThat(result.getViewName()).isEqualTo("views/ui-error");
        assertThat(result.getModel())
                .containsEntry("pageTitle", "Erreur technique")
                .containsEntry("iconPath", "/images/icons/tools.svg")
                .containsEntry(
                        "title",
                        "Oups, un problème<br>technique est survenu.")
                .containsEntry(
                        "message",
                        "Nous n’avons pas pu charger les données nécessaires pour le moment.")
                .containsEntry(
                        "strongMessage",
                        "Réessayez dans quelques minutes. Si le problème persiste, contactez votre Zone Manager pour obtenir de l’aide.");
    }

    @Test
    void noSalesPoint_shouldReturnNoSalesPointErrorPage() {
        ModelAndView result = errorController.noSalesPoint();

        assertThat(result.getViewName()).isEqualTo("views/ui-error");
        assertThat(result.getModel())
                .containsEntry("pageTitle", "Point de vente non défini")
                .containsEntry("iconPath", "/images/icons/warning.svg")
                .containsEntry(
                        "title",
                        "Oups, votre point de vente<br>n’est pas encore défini")
                .containsEntry(
                        "message",
                        "Votre compte n’est pas associé à un point de vente. Vous ne pouvez donc pas accéder à la plateforme partenaire Cetelem.")
                .containsEntry(
                        "strongMessage",
                        "Veuillez contacter votre Zone Manager pour recevoir de l’aide.");
    }
}
```

Imports:

```java
import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;
import org.springframework.web.servlet.ModelAndView;

import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;
```

You can remove this annotation because the test has no mocks:

```java
@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)
```

## Add coverage for callback failure

In `AuthControllerTest`, add:

```java
@Test
void callback_shouldRedirectToTechnicalErrorPage_whenAuthenticationFails()
        throws Exception {

    when(authService.handleCallback(anyString(), anyString()))
            .thenThrow(new TechnicalException("Token exchange failed"));

    mockMvc.perform(get("/auth/callback")
                    .param("code", "invalid-code")
                    .param("state", "invalid-state"))
            .andExpect(status().is3xxRedirection())
            .andExpect(redirectedUrl("/arthur-core/error/technical"));
}
```

This test proves the user sees your French UI error page instead of the PF XML error response.
